description:
&lt;p&gt;An new opportunity has arisen at Queen Victoria Memorial hospital Inpatients rehabilitation unit, for the position of Healthcare Assistant.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;We are a 22 bedded ward where team work and multidisciplinary working are paramount. Job Responsibilities would involve, supporting the patients with personal hygiene needs, hydration and meal needs together with maintaining patient safety.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Working pattern would be shifts Long days and Nights.&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;The successful candidate will have:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Previous experience in hospital/nursing home setting&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Awareness of personal care needs&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Awareness of needs of older people&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Awareness of Health and Safety at work&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good written and oral communication skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Good team skills&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;In return, we can offer you:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;ul&gt;
&lt;li&gt;5% on top of basic salary high cost allowance supplement subject to a minimum payment of 31,034&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;27 days holiday rising to 33 days (depending on NHS Trust service) plus bank holidays (pro rata where applicable)&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;One of the UK&#39;s best pension schemes&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Special Leave for family and personal reasons&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Car Lease Scheme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Eye Care Vouchers&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;Employee Assistance Programme&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;li&gt;NHS Discounts&lt;/li&gt;
&lt;/ul&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Hertfordshire Community NHS Trust is voted as one of the &#39;Top 100 Best Places to Work&#39; (Health Service Journal). Our CQC rating is of &#39;Good&#39;&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;You must hold a full valid driving licence and access to a car to use regularly for business purposes is essential (unless you have a disability as defined by the Equality Act 2010).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Interview 18th November&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;For further details / informal visits contact:&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Name: Justine Fraser&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Job title: Ward Manager&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Email address: Justine.fraser1@nhs.net&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;Telephone number: 01438841803 / 07879840574&lt;/p&gt;
